raw_data.title: IT Business Specialist VII
raw_data.description: Includes all labor efforts related to IT Automated Information Systems Design and Integration project planning and scheduling, market research and acquisition planning, and cost and task estimating. Performs complex IT evaluations of existing procedures, processes, techniques, models and systems related to management problems or contractual issues that would require a report, and recommends solutions. Principal duties may include preparing technology work breakdown structures, charts, tables, graphs and diagrams to assist in analyzing problems. Provides daily supervision and direction to administrative staff, and assists with program and project management.

raw_data.title: IT Engineer/Analyst III
raw_data.description: While supervised, performs a variety of IT tasks involving design and implementation, including personnel, hardware, software and support for facilities and equipment. Performs with some latitude for un?reviewed actions and decisions.

raw_data.title: IT Junior Engineer/Analyst I
raw_data.description: While supervised, assists in defining and executing IT engineering activities within a project. These activities may consist of technology resources and facilities management, database planning and design, systems analysis and design, network services, programming, conversion and implementation support, network services project management, data/records management, and other services. Performs IT engineering systems analysis and design, database planning and design, and network services. Develops and staffs an engineering management plan. Provides project engineers with conversion and implementation support, as required. Performs other duties as assigned.

raw_data.title: IT Manager VII
raw_data.description: Directs the performance of a variety of related projects, which may be organized by technology, program or client. Oversees the technology development for application, marketing and resource allocation within program client base. Responsible for the effective management of orders and personnel and is accountable for the quality and timely delivery of all IT contractual items. Operates within client guidance contractual limitations and company business

raw_data.title: IT Project Manager VII
raw_data.description: Manages project operations. Ensures that technology production schedules are met. Ensures that IT system resources are used effectively. Coordinates the resolution of IT production?related problems.  Ensures that proper relationships are established between customers, teaming partners and vendors to facilitate the delivery of information technology services. Provides network services project management, data and records management and other services. Supervises staff operations.

raw_data.title: IT Senior Engineer/Analyst V
raw_data.description: Performs a variety of broad IT engineering tasks, either independently or under supervision, involving design and implementation, including personnel, hardware, software, and support facilities and equipment. Supervises a team of IT engineers through project completion. Plans and performs engineering research, design development and other assignments in conformance with design, engineering and customer specifications. Supervises team of IT engineers through project completion. Manages major technical and engineering projects of higher complexity and importance than those normally assigned to lower level engineers. Coordinates the activities of engineers and technicians assigned to specific engineering projects. Assists with database planning and design, systems analysis and design, network services, programming and conversion and implementation support. Performs other duties as assigned.

raw_data.title: IT Senior Scientist/SME I
raw_data.description: Expert in single or multiple technical disciplines providing expert knowledge and insight into specific areas of science, technology and automated information systems design and integration. Guides the development and application of this knowledge to the IT project. Independently performs a variety of system design and integration tasks where subject matter expertise is required. Supervises and guides a broad team of technical staff/engineer. Plans and performs required research, design evaluation, technical development, system integration planning and other tasks in specific technical areas. Responsible for highly complex technical/engineering tasks. Coordinates and guides the activities of technical staff assigned to specific tasks. Supervises database planning and design, systems analysis and design, network services, programming, conversion and implementation support, data/records management, and other services. May perform other duties as required.

raw_data.title: IT Senior Scientist/SME III
raw_data.description: Expert in single or multiple technical disciplines providing expert knowledge and insight into specific areas of science, technology and automated information systems design and integration. Guides the IT development and application of this knowledge to the project. Independently performs a variety of system design and integration tasks where subject matter expertise is required. Supervises and guides a broad team of technical staff/engineer. Plans and performs required research, design evaluation, technical development, system integration planning and other tasks in specific technical areas. Responsible for highly complex technical/engineering tasks. Coordinates and guides the activities of technical staff assigned to specific tasks. Supervises database planning and design, systems analysis and design, network services, programming, conversion and implementation support, data/records management, and other services. May perform other duties as required.

raw_data.title: IT Technician V
raw_data.description: Works while supervised to perform a variety of broad IT engineering tasks involving design and implementation of automated information systems. Supports the planning and performance of IT engineering and customer specifications. Supports the technical and engineering activities related to the development and integration of testing of a project assigned to higher level engineers. Works under the supervision of a senior IT engineer or project manager. Provides database planning and design, systems analysis and design, network services, programming, conversion and implementation support, network services project management, data/records management, and other services. Performs other duties as assigned.
